{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"2b43f4d8-8d82-4521-a9b2-372a2a27980d","content":"Here's the summary:\n\n**No, you don't need `TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport` anymore.** That property was the .NET 9 opt-in to route `dotnet test` through Microsoft.Testing.Platform. In .NET 10, MTP is the **default** — `dotnet test` uses it automatically.\n\nYour project already has the only thing that matters:\n- **`EnableMSTestRunner`** — builds your test project as an MTP executable\n- **`OutputType Exe`** — required for the above\n\nJust run `dotnet test` as usual and it will go through MTP natively. If you ever need to fall back to the legacy VSTest pipeline, you can set `<TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>false</TestingPlatformDotnetTestSupport>`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bedfc900-370f-4d0e-ae04-a39b14609a13","outputTokens":194,"requestId":"1BD0:2DDEB2:206EC6E:23DB930:6A03CF88"},"id":"ce87cda5-b212-481e-be27-15b3ffeef270","timestamp":"2026-05-13T01:10:37.974Z","parentId":"abc6f588-eb62-4265-b822-36ae54d5f736"}
